    q("Bicep vs Terraform Decision Framework", "IaC", "Very Common",
      "Walk through your decision framework for Bicep vs Terraform on an Azure-only .NET platform.",
      "Azure-only greenfield → Bicep (day-zero resources, ARM-backed state). Multi-cloud or existing TF investment → Terraform. Document in ADR with 5-year migration cost estimate.",
      "**Decision matrix:**\n| Factor | Bicep | Terraform |\n|--------|-------|----------|\n| Azure coverage | Day-zero | Slight lag |\n| State management | ARM tracks | Remote backend required |\n| Multi-cloud | No | Yes |\n| Team skills | ARM DSL learning curve | HCL widely known |\n| Module registry | ACR OCI | Terraform Registry |\n\n**Hybrid:** Bicep for Azure PaaS; Terraform for Cloudflare + Azure. Clear ownership boundary per resource group.\n\n**Architect:** Coexistence OK — never manage same resource in both tools.",
      "IaC choice is long-lived — interviewers want criteria not tribal preference.",
      "Pulumi/C#? — Option when team wants IaC in C# — evaluate team appetite.",
      "Switching cost? — High — pick deliberately in ADR.",
      "Terraform for 100% Azure with no multi-cloud plan",
      "Same resource in Bicep and Terraform",
      "No ADR documenting IaC choice"),
    q("Bicep Module Composition", "Bicep", "Common",
      "How do you compose Bicep modules for a .NET platform landing zone?",
      "Layer modules: `network.bicep` → `keyVault.bicep` → `appService.bicep` → `appInsights.bicep`. Parent template orchestrates; modules expose minimal params and outputs.",
      "**Structure:**\n```\nmodules/\n  networking/vnet.bicep\n  compute/appServicePlan.bicep\n  security/keyVault.bicep\nmain.bicep  # wires modules\n```\n\n**Rules:**\n- Modules 50–150 lines — not monolithic 800-line file\n- Outputs: `keyVaultUri`, `appServiceName` for pipeline consumption\n- Semantic versioning via Bicep registry OCI artifacts\n\n**Architect:** Module catalog mirrors platform service offerings.",
      "Module composition enables environment promotion with same building blocks.",
      "Nested vs registry modules? — Registry for cross-subscription reuse.",
      "Too granular? — Balance copy-paste vs 40-module dependency graph.",
      "800-line monolithic main.bicep",
      "Copy-paste module per environment",
      "Modules with hardcoded prod SKU"),
    q("Terraform State Backend on Azure Storage", "Terraform", "Common",
      "Configure Terraform remote state on Azure Storage for production workloads.",
      "Storage account with versioning, encryption, private endpoint, RBAC restricted to platform pipeline SP. Separate container per environment.",
      "**Backend config:**\n```hcl\nbackend \"azurerm\" {\n  resource_group_name  = \"rg-tfstate-prod\"\n  storage_account_name = \"sttfstateprod\"\n  container_name       = \"tfstate-order\"\n  key                  = \"prod.terraform.tfstate\"\n}\n```\n\n**Hardening:**\n- Blob versioning enabled — recover corrupted state\n- `Storage Blob Data Contributor` only for pipeline SP\n- No public network access\n\n**Architect:** State is DR-critical — backup strategy documented.",
      "Remote state is prerequisite for team IaC — local state is solo-dev only.",
      "State per env vs workspace? — Separate state files for prod isolation preferred.",
      "Sensitive values in state? — Encrypt; restrict access; use sensitive outputs carefully.",
      "Local terraform.tfstate committed to Git",
      "Single state file for dev and prod",
      "No blob versioning on state account"),
    q("Terraform State Locking", "Terraform", "Common",
      "How does state locking prevent concurrent Terraform applies and what breaks it?",
      "Azure backend uses blob lease for lock during `apply`. Concurrent apply fails with lock error — prevents state corruption.",
      "**Failure modes:**\n- CI job killed mid-apply — stale lock remains\n- Fix: `terraform force-unlock LOCK_ID` after verifying no running apply\n\n**Prevention:**\n- Timeout on pipeline jobs\n- One apply per state file at a time (`concurrency` group in GitHub Actions)\n- Never apply prod from laptop while pipeline runs\n\n**Architect:** Locking is why remote state mandatory for teams — local state has no lock.",
      "State locking incidents are common ops scenarios — know unlock procedure.",
      "DynamoDB locking on AWS? — Same concept — Azure uses blob lease.",
      "Bicep locking? — ARM deployment locking at resource group level — different mechanism.",
      "Two pipeline applies to prod simultaneously",
      "Force-unlock without checking running jobs",
      "No concurrency control in CI pipeline"),
    q("IaC Drift Detection Automation", "IaC", "Common",
      "Automate infrastructure drift detection for Bicep and Terraform managed resources.",
      "Nightly scheduled pipeline: `terraform plan -detailed-exitcode` or `az deployment group what-if` — alert on non-empty diff. Azure Policy denies unauthorized changes.",
      "**Layers:**\n1. **Prevent:** Policy denies public IP, enforces SKU whitelist\n2. **Detect:** Nightly plan/what-if in read-only mode\n3. **Remediate:** Auto-apply correct state OR backport portal hotfix to IaC within 24h\n\n**Alert:** Slack message with diff summary — assign owner.\n\n**Architect:** Black Friday manual scale-up must be backported or reverted Monday.",
      "Drift detection closes the loop on IaC governance.",
      "Intentional break-glass? — Ticket + 24h backport SLA.",
      "Drift on auto-scaled resources? — Exclude scale sets from strict drift or use target tracking in IaC.",
      "Portal changes never reconciled to IaC",
      "Drift detected but no owner assigned",
      "Auto-apply drift without human review on prod"),
    q("Bicep What-If Preview", "Bicep", "Common",
      "How do you use Bicep what-if in pull request workflows?",
      "CI runs `az deployment group what-if` with read-only SP; bot comments predicted creates/modifies/deletes on PR. Reviewers see blast radius before merge.",
      "**Pipeline:**\n```bash\naz deployment group what-if \\\n  --resource-group rg-order-staging \\\n  --template-file main.bicep \\\n  --parameters @staging.bicepparam\n```\n\n**PR comment:** Parse JSON output — highlight destructive changes (delete, SKU downgrade).\n\n**Architect:** What-if is Bicep's plan equivalent — mandatory for prod-bound PRs.",
      "What-if prevents surprise deletions — common IaC incident source.",
      "What-if vs validate? — Validate syntax only; what-if shows actual ARM changes.",
      "Scope? — Resource group deployment for most .NET workloads; subscription for landing zone.",
      "First visibility of changes at apply time",
      "What-if skipped for 'small' PRs",
      "No highlight of destructive changes in PR"),
    q("Policy as Code with Azure Policy", "Governance", "Common",
      "Design Azure Policy initiatives that complement Bicep deployments for a .NET platform.",
      "IaC deploys desired state; Policy catches portal drift and non-IaC creation paths. Initiative bundles: require tags, deny public storage, allowed regions, enforce Managed Identity.",
      "**Example policies:**\n- `Deny` — Storage account public access\n- `AuditIfNotExists` — Diagnostic settings on App Service\n- `DeployIfNotExists` — Auto-enable Defender\n\n**Mapping:** Policy initiative per compliance framework (SOC 2 CC6, CC7).\n\n**Architect:** Policy exemption process with expiry — not permanent exceptions.",
      "Policy as code is defense in depth beyond IaC discipline.",
      "Terraform Sentinel? — Plan-time policy for TF shops — Azure Policy for ARM resources.",
      "Policy vs RBAC? — Policy restricts resource config; RBAC restricts who can create.",
      "Policy so strict developers use shadow subscriptions",
      "No exemption workflow",
      "IaC-only governance without Policy"),
    q("Bicep Parameter Files Per Environment", "Bicep", "Common",
      "How do `.bicepparam` files enable safe multi-environment deployments?",
      "Same `main.bicep` module; `dev.bicepparam`, `staging.bicepparam`, `prod.bicepparam` differ SKUs, capacity, feature flags. Never fork template per environment.",
      "**Example:**\n```bicep\n// prod.bicepparam\nusing 'main.bicep'\nparam appServiceSku = 'P2v3'\nparam sqlSku = 'GP_Gen5_4'\nparam enableZoneRedundant = true\n```\n\n**CI:** PR triggers what-if for all environments. Prod apply requires approval.\n\n**Architect:** Parameter files are promotion mechanism — template unchanged across envs.",
      "Parameter files embody DRY multi-environment IaC.",
      "Secrets in bicepparam? — Reference Key Vault — never plain text.",
      "Default params? — `main.bicep` defaults for dev only — prod explicit in bicepparam.",
      "Separate main-prod.bicep fork",
      "Prod SKU hardcoded in shared module",
      "Secrets committed in bicepparam files"),
    q("Key Vault Secret References in IaC", "Security", "Common",
      "Reference Key Vault secrets from Bicep without exposing values in templates.",
      "Use `getSecret()` in Bicep with user-assigned MI granted Key Vault Secrets User. App Service `keyVaultReference` for runtime — secret never in ARM template output.",
      "**Pattern:**\n```bicep\nresource app 'Microsoft.Web/sites@2022-03-01' = {\n  properties: {\n    siteConfig: {\n      appSettings: [{\n        name: 'ConnectionStrings__Default'\n        value: '@Microsoft.KeyVault(SecretUri=${sqlConnSecretUri})'\n      }]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Pipeline:** Deploy MI + Key Vault access before app referencing secrets.\n\n**Architect:** No secrets in Git, state, or pipeline logs — ever.",
      "Secret references separate deployment-time from secret value exposure.",
      "Key Vault purge protection? — Enable on prod — prevent accidental secret deletion.",
      "Rotation? — Update secret version in Key Vault — app picks up new version if configured.",
      "Connection string in bicepparam plain text",
      "Key Vault secret in Terraform output",
      "Secret echoed in what-if output logged publicly"),
    q("CI Validation for Bicep Pull Requests", "IaC", "Common",
      "What Bicep validation runs on every pull request before merge?",
      "`bicep build`, `bicep lint`, what-if against staging RG, Checkov/static analysis, and optional PSRule for Azure best practices.",
      "**CI pipeline:**\n1. `az bicep build --file main.bicep` — compile check\n2. `bicep lint` — linter rules\n3. Checkov scan — security misconfigurations\n4. What-if — predicted changes\n5. Cost estimate — `az cost management` preview if available\n\n**Merge gate:** All pass + platform team review for networking changes.\n\n**Architect:** IaC PR checks as rigorous as application PR checks.",
      "CI validation catches NSG open to world before apply.",
      "Module registry publish? — Separate pipeline on tag — consumers pin version.",
      "Breaking module change? — Semver major bump in registry.",
      "Validate only on prod apply",
      "No lint rules enabled",
      "Skip what-if for time savings"),
    q("Terraform Workspaces vs Separate State", "Terraform", "Common",
      "When use Terraform workspaces vs separate state files per environment?",
      "Separate state files per environment for production isolation. Workspaces for ephemeral dev sandboxes only — workspace switching error risks prod apply.",
      "**Separate state (recommended prod):**\n```\nbackend key = \"prod/order.tfstate\"\nbackend key = \"staging/order.tfstate\"\n```\n\n**Workspaces:** Same backend, different workspace name — lighter but `-workspace=prod` typo danger.\n\n**Architect:** Prod state isolation is non-negotiable — separate backend key or storage container.",
      "Workspace vs state is common Terraform interview trap.",
      "Terragrunt? — Wrapper for DRY backend config per env.",
      "Ephemeral env? — Workspace or separate state destroyed on PR close.",
      "Prod and dev share workspace",
      "Workspace select in script without confirmation",
      "No concurrency lock per state"),
    q("Import Existing Azure Resources", "IaC", "Common",
      "Import manually created Azure resources into Bicep or Terraform management.",
      "Inventory resource → author matching template → `terraform import` or Bicep `existing` + incremental adoption → verify plan shows zero changes → enable Policy.",
      "**Terraform:**\n```bash\nterraform import azurerm_resource_group.rg /subscriptions/.../resourceGroups/rg-order\n```\n\n**Bicep:** `resource kv 'Microsoft.KeyVault/vaults@...' existing = { name: 'kv-prod' }` then expand to full definition.\n\n**Phasing:** Import prod SQL first (highest drift risk), dev storage later.\n\n**Architect:** `az bicep decompile` is starting point — never production-ready without review.",
      "Brownfield import is reality — architects phase by blast radius.",
      "Delete and recreate? — Data loss — avoid for stateful resources.",
      "Import entire subscription day one? — Phased by resource group.",
      "Decompile output deployed unreviewed",
      "Import without drift prevention Policy",
      "Managing same VM in portal and IaC"),
    q("Azure Resource Naming Conventions", "IaC", "Common",
      "Define a resource naming convention for a multi-team Azure .NET platform.",
      "`{type}-{workload}-{env}-{region}-{instance}` — e.g., `app-order-prod-eus-01`, `kv-shared-prod-eus`, `sql-order-stg-eus`. Enforce via Policy and Bicep parameters.",
      "**Components:**\n- **Type prefix:** `app`, `func`, `sql`, `st`, `kv`, `rg`\n- **Workload:** `order`, `payment`, `shared`\n- **Env:** `dev`, `stg`, `prod`\n- **Region:** `eus`, `weu`\n\n**Limits:** Storage account 3–24 lowercase alphanumeric — abbreviate.\n\n**Architect:** Naming in platform module — teams pass `workloadName` only; convention applied automatically.",
      "Naming enables automation, cost allocation, and on-call clarity.",
      "Global uniqueness? — Storage and Key Vault names global — include random suffix if needed.",
      "Rename resource? — Often recreate — get naming right at provision.",
      "Random portal-generated names",
      "Different convention per team",
      "No naming in IaC modules — manual each time"),
    q("Tagging Strategy Enforcement", "FinOps", "Common",
      "Enforce mandatory tags through IaC and Azure Policy for cost allocation.",
      "Mandatory tags: `Environment`, `CostCenter`, `Owner`, `Application`, `ManagedBy`. Policy `deny` if missing. Bicep module applies tags to all child resources.",
      "**Policy:**\n```json\n\"deny\" if tags.CostCenter is empty on resource creation\n```\n\n**IaC:**\n```bicep\nvar tags = {\n  Environment: environment\n  CostCenter: costCenter\n  Owner: ownerEmail\n}\n```\n\n**Limit:** 5–7 mandatory tags — more causes tag sprawl and deploy friction.\n\n**Architect:** Tags at provision time — retrofitting 500 resources is painful.",
      "Tagging connects IaC to FinOps showback/chargeback.",
      "Inherited tags? — Resource group tags propagate — set at RG in module.",
      "Tag audit? — Monthly report untagged resources — Policy audit mode first.",
      "15 mandatory tags blocking dev velocity",
      "Tags optional in modules",
      "Audit-only Policy never upgraded to deny"),
    q("Landing Zone Bicep Modules", "IaC", "Common",
      "What belongs in Azure landing zone Bicep modules for .NET workloads?",
      "Hub-spoke networking, Log Analytics workspace, Key Vault, ACR, App Service Plan baseline, diagnostic settings, Private DNS — product teams deploy app modules into spoke.",
      "**Module layers:**\n1. **Platform landing zone** — subscription vending, policy, networking\n2. **Workload landing zone** — RG, App Insights, app plan\n3. **Application module** — App Service, SQL, Redis per service\n\n**CAF alignment:** Microsoft Cloud Adoption Framework reference implementations.\n\n**Architect:** Product team cannot create VNet — platform provides spoke subscription.",
      "Landing zones scale governance — architects define platform vs product boundary.",
      "Terraform ALZ? — Azure Landing Zones — enterprise-scale alternative to custom Bicep.",
      "Subscription vending? — Pipeline creates spoke per team from template.",
      "Every team creates own VNet and firewall",
      "Landing zone monolith never updated",
      "No separation platform vs application modules"),
    q("Ephemeral Environments with IaC", "IaC", "Common",
      "Provision ephemeral PR preview environments with Bicep and tear down on merge.",
      "PR opened → pipeline deploys `rg-order-pr-1234` with App Service + SQL basic tier → comment preview URL → PR closed/merged → `az group delete`.",
      "**Cost controls:**\n- Auto-delete after 24h TTL tag\n- Budget alert per PR RG\n- Shared SQL server with per-PR database optional\n\n**IaC:** Same modules as staging; `pr.bicepparam` with minimal SKUs.\n\n**Architect:** Ephemeral envs need DNS wildcard `pr-1234.dev.contoso.com` and Key Vault access for test secrets.",
      "Ephemeral environments accelerate integration feedback — IDP feature.",
      "Data seeding? — Flyway/EF migrate on deploy — synthetic data only.",
      "Shared vs isolated ephemeral? — Isolated RG safer; shared cheaper.",
      "PR environments never destroyed — cost spiral",
      "Ephemeral prod SKU sizing",
      "No TTL or budget alert on preview RGs"),
    q("GitOps Argo CD vs Pipeline Deploy", "GitOps", "Common",
      "Compare Argo CD GitOps and push-based pipeline deploy for AKS vs App Service.",
      "AKS with 10+ services → Argo CD reconciles cluster to Git desired state. App Service + Bicep → push pipeline apply is simpler and equivalent desired-state pattern.",
      "**GitOps (pull):**\n- Cluster pulls manifests from Git\n- Drift auto-corrected\n- Rollback = git revert\n\n**Push pipeline:**\n- CI calls `az deployment` or `kubectl apply`\n- Simpler for PaaS\n- Drift requires what-if detection\n\n**Architect:** Match model to compute — don't mandate Argo for 3 App Service APIs.",
      "GitOps is not universal — platform-dependent architecture choice.",
      "Flux vs Argo? — Both valid GitOps — organizational preference.",
      "App Service GitOps? — Bicep in Git + pipeline is functional GitOps.",
      "kubectl apply from developer laptop to prod",
      "Argo CD without understanding reconciliation loop",
      "GitOps mandated for simple PaaS workload"),
    q("IaC Security Testing with Checkov", "IaC", "Common",
      "Integrate Checkov into IaC CI to catch misconfigurations before apply.",
      "Run `checkov -d .` on Bicep/Terraform/ARM in PR pipeline. Gate on CRITICAL; suppress false positives with documented skip comments.",
      "**Common catches:**\n- Storage account public access enabled\n- NSG allows 0.0.0.0/0 on 3389\n- Key Vault soft delete disabled\n- SQL no TLS enforcement\n\n**Integration:**\n```yaml\n- run: pip install checkov && checkov -d infra/ --framework bicep\n```\n\n**Architect:** Checkov complements what-if — security rules what-if may not evaluate.",
      "Static IaC analysis is shift-left for infrastructure security.",
      "tfsec vs Checkov? — Overlapping — pick one org standard.",
      "Suppressions? — `# checkov:skip=CKV_AZURE_33 reason=...` with ticket reference.",
      "Checkov only run manually",
      "All findings ignored",
      "No IaC scan in CI pipeline"),
    q("Blast Radius via Resource Groups", "IaC", "Common",
      "How do resource group boundaries limit IaC blast radius?",
      "Scope deployments per RG: `rg-order-prod` contains only order service resources. Failed apply or bad delete affects one workload — not entire subscription.",
      "**Patterns:**\n- One RG per microservice per environment\n- Network hub in separate RG — peering not co-deployed with app\n- State file scoped to RG deployment\n\n**Deletion:** `az group delete` on wrong RG is recoverable if soft-delete enabled — still dangerous.\n\n**Architect:** RG design in landing zone ADR — teams cannot deploy to shared networking RG.",
      "Blast radius containment is IaC architecture fundamentals.",
      "Subscription per env? — Further isolation for regulated — higher overhead.",
      "Locks? — CanNotDelete lock on prod RG — prevent accidental group delete.",
      "Entire subscription in one template apply",
      "Shared RG for 12 microservices",
      "No delete locks on production resource groups"),
