    q("Capacity Headroom Planning", "Capacity", "Common",
      "How much headroom above peak load should production maintain?",
      "20–40% headroom above measured peak for compute. 50% for critical path before auto-scale lag catches up. Load test at 2× expected peak annually.",
      "**Headroom covers:** Auto-scale delay (2–5 min), deploy surge, viral spike, AZ failure (lose 33% capacity).\n\n**Document:** Peak RPS from last Black Friday + growth factor.\n\n**Cost trade-off:** Reserved baseline + burst on-demand for headroom.",
      "Headroom is explicit capacity NFR — not accidental over-provision.",
      "Chaos test headroom? — Kill AZ during load test — validate surviving capacity.",
      "Queue-based absorption? — Queue adds temporal headroom — bounded buffer.",
      "100% utilized at peak — no scale room",
      "Never load test above production peak",
      "Headroom only on CPU not connections"),
    q("Performance Budgets at Scale", "Performance", "Common",
      "Define performance budget for search API at 50K RPS.",
      "p99 < 150ms end-to-end. Max 2 internal hops. Elasticsearch query < 80ms. Serialization < 10ms. Zero N+1 DB calls on search path.",
      "**Enforcement:** Load test gate in CI on PR touching search. RUM vs synthetic gap tracked.\n\n**Budget breakdown:** Network 20ms + gateway 10ms + service 80ms + ES 80ms — identify slack.\n\n**Regression:** Alert when p99 degrades 10% week-over-week.",
      "Performance budgets make NFR measurable and enforceable.",
      "Mobile budget? — Add 100ms RTT for 3G — separate target.",
      "Third-party API in budget? — Include or async exclude from sync path.",
      "No per-component budget",
      "Budget only measured in dev laptop",
      "Ignore regression alerts"),
    q("Load Test Interpretation", "Testing", "Common",
      "Load test: p50 50ms, p99 2000ms, errors 0.1% at target RPS. Interpret.",
      "Tail latency problem — likely GC pause, lock contention, slow dependency, or connection pool wait. 0.1% errors may be timeout under load — investigate before launch.",
      "**Analysis steps:**\n1. Trace slow p99 requests — distributed tracing\n2. Check DB slow query log during test\n3. Thread pool queue depth correlation\n4. Compare ramp vs steady state\n\n**Pass criteria:** p99 within SLO at 1.5× target RPS with <0.01% errors.",
      "Architects interpret load tests — not just run and screenshot.",
      "Coordinated omission? — Gatling/k6 handle better than naive JMeter — know tool bias.",
      "Soak test? — 4h run detects memory leak invisible in 10min test.",
      "Only report p50",
      "Ignore 0.1% errors as noise",
      "Load test without production-like data volume"),
